 1. FFC Turbine Potsdam Logo
Frauenfußballclub Turbine Potsdam 71 e. V., commonly known as 1. FFC Turbine Potsdam, is a German women’s football club located in Potsdam, Brandenburg. They are one of the most successful women’s football teams in Germany, having won six Frauen-Bundesliga championships and two UEFA Women’s Champions League titles. They play in the Karl-Liebknecht-Stadion in the Babelsberg district of Potsdam, and their biggest rivals are Eintracht Frankfurt. Before the reunification of Germany, Turbine Potsdam were one of the predominant teams in East German women’s football.
